H0.text: Which wife of Henry VIII had already married twice before she became queen, and married for a fourth time after Henry's death. Catherine of Aragon

H1.text: Which wife of Henry VIII had already married twice before she became queen, and married for a fourth time after Henry's death. Anne Boleyn

H2.text: Which wife of Henry VIII had already married twice before she became queen, and married for a fourth time after Henry's death. Jane Seymour

H3.text: Which wife of Henry VIII had already married twice before she became queen, and married for a fourth time after Henry's death. Lady Latimer

A4.text: Catherine of Aragon was Queen of England as the first wife of King Henry VIII from their marriage on 11 June 1509 until its annulment on 23 May 1533.

A5.text: Catherine had first come to England to be bride to Henry's brother Arthur, Prince of Wales, who died soon after their marriage.

A6.text: Anne returned to England in early 1522, to marry her cousin James Butler, 9th Earl of Ormond; the marriage plans were broken off, and instead, she secured a post at court as maid of honour to Henry VIII's wife, Catherine of Aragon.

A7.text: Catherine Parr, later Queen of England.

A8.text: Catherine of Aragon (16 December 1485 – 7 January 1536; Spanish: Catalina de Aragón) was Henry's first wife.

A9.text: Catherine was originally married to Arthur, Henry's older brother.

A10.text: Anne Boleyn was Henry's second wife and the mother of Elizabeth I.

A11.text: Jane Seymour was Henry's third wife.

A12.text: About six months after Henry's death, she married her fourth and final husband, Thomas Seymour, 1st Baron Seymour of Sudeley.

A13.text: Catherine had previously been the wife of Henry's older brother Arthur.
